canonical:
  title: 開樽愛月
  author: 孫舜孝
  language: lzh
  text: 月白東巒便照堂一樽涵得幾多光只憐些子淸輝發不許庸人取次嘗
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 開樽愛月
  author: 孫舜孝
  language: lzh
  text: 月白東巒便照堂。一樽涵得幾多光。只憐些子淸輝發。不許庸人取次嘗。
korean:
  title: 개준 애월
  author: 손순효
  language: kor
  text: |-
    동쪽 봉우리의 흰 달이 갑자기 마루를 비추거니
    한 항아리에 얼마나 많은 빛을 담을 수 있겠는가
    다만 조그만 이것이 내는 맑은 빛을 사랑하여
    용렬한 사람 함부로 맛보는 것을 허락하지 않는다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0350&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Opening a Vessel to Admire the Moon
  author: Sun Shun-hyo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The moon rises white above the eastern peaks, suddenly illuminating the hall.
    How much of its radiance can a single vessel hold?
    I treasure only this subtle gleam it casts—
    I grant no common soul permission to taste it carelessly.
  footnotes:
    - The poem uses the metaphor of wine in a vessel to represent the distilled essence of moonlight, suggesting that true beauty is rare and not for indiscriminate consumption.
